WEBVTT

00:02.670 --> 00:06.130
-♪
-[gobbling]

00:06.132 --> 00:08.382
[folk music playing]

00:18.519 --> 00:20.227
[gobbles]

00:24.650 --> 00:26.442
[crunching, gulps]

00:26.444 --> 00:28.485
♪

00:40.249 --> 00:41.331
D'oh!

00:42.501 --> 00:44.543
♪

00:49.258 --> 00:51.258
♪

01:06.734 --> 01:08.692
-[buzzer sounding]
-huh?

01:11.238 --> 01:15.115
Our first thanksgiving
since homer passed away.

01:15.117 --> 01:16.992
-More turkey, please.
-Aw.

01:16.994 --> 01:19.995
Thank god we still have
his hologram.

01:23.876 --> 01:25.459
[clanking]

01:25.461 --> 01:26.919
All right, everyone.

01:26.921 --> 01:29.505
Get out
your remembrance candles.

01:31.425 --> 01:34.134
Granny lisa,
why do we light a candle

01:34.136 --> 01:35.761
Every thanksgiving?

01:35.763 --> 01:38.097
In remembrance of
the great blackout

01:38.099 --> 01:40.224
That almost destroyed our town

01:40.226 --> 01:44.061
When we actually had to
write things down by hand.

01:44.063 --> 01:45.771
(gasping, whimpering)

01:45.773 --> 01:48.440
It started on
a cold November day.

01:48.442 --> 01:52.861
Back when you could actually see
snow outside of a museum.

01:52.863 --> 01:54.071
[wind howling]

01:54.073 --> 01:57.032
[kent]<i> goodbye, autumn,</i>
<i> hello, novem-brrr.</i>

01:57.034 --> 01:59.868
A powerful winter storm
is headed our way.

01:59.870 --> 02:02.913
-Homie.
-♪<i> aloha 'oe</i> ♪

02:02.915 --> 02:04.331
Homie, wake up.

02:04.333 --> 02:08.418
♪<i> aloha 'oe...</i> ♪ [groans]

02:08.420 --> 02:11.755
This isn't hawaii.
It's never hawaii.

02:11.757 --> 02:13.757
It's just stupid america.

02:13.759 --> 02:16.093
There's a winter storm
coming in.

02:16.095 --> 02:17.928
[scoffs] winter storm.

02:17.930 --> 02:19.263
I refuse to be scared

02:19.265 --> 02:21.473
Unless there's
some terrifying new term for it.

02:21.475 --> 02:24.059
It's an arctic blast
with a bomb cyclone

02:24.061 --> 02:26.103
And a chance of firenado,

02:26.105 --> 02:28.397
Or as we in the news business
call it,

02:28.399 --> 02:30.774
-And "arcticonado."
-[homer screams]

02:30.776 --> 02:32.484
None of us call it that, kent.

02:32.486 --> 02:34.528
Pipe down, arnie.
I'm selling hoodies.

02:34.530 --> 02:35.904
[homer humming]

02:36.574 --> 02:38.323
-Homer, this is important.
-Hmm?

02:38.325 --> 02:41.201
Did you put up the storm windows
like you promised?

02:41.203 --> 02:43.787
[lisa]
<i>there are two things I've leaned</i>
<i> are completely worthless:</i>

02:43.789 --> 02:48.208
<i> Scented toilet paper and</i>
<i> a promise from homer simpsons.</i>

02:48.210 --> 02:50.127
-[wind whistles]
-[ralph whimpering]

02:50.462 --> 02:53.338
I'll put 'em up
right after work.

02:53.340 --> 02:55.591
You're going to work in that?

02:55.593 --> 02:58.760
It's hawaiian day,
and the guys elected me

02:58.762 --> 03:00.295
King kamehameha.

03:00.297 --> 03:02.931
Let the goofing off at work
commence.

03:02.933 --> 03:04.641
[toots]

03:07.188 --> 03:10.063
-[wind whistles]
-[homer groans]

03:10.065 --> 03:12.232
Ew, bacon.

03:12.610 --> 03:14.193
Mmm.

03:16.155 --> 03:18.280
-[wind whistles]
-[gasps]

03:18.282 --> 03:19.531
[grunting]

03:20.951 --> 03:22.534
[exhales]

03:22.536 --> 03:26.330
Now, kids, I know the forecast
says it's triple-mitten weather,

03:26.332 --> 03:30.375
But the good news is, it's less
than one week till turkey day.

03:30.377 --> 03:33.545
Mom! Can we please not
call it "turkey day"?

03:33.547 --> 03:36.757
You're celebrating
the slaughter of a living thing.

03:36.759 --> 03:38.800
Lisa, you always
slaughter the mood.

03:38.802 --> 03:42.971
You know, there are some amazing
faux turkeys to eat now.

03:42.973 --> 03:44.139
Said no one, ever.

03:44.141 --> 03:45.891
Right now,
they're perfecting the taste,

03:45.893 --> 03:49.853
But in the future, faux turkeys
will taste really good.

03:49.855 --> 03:51.438
[munching] hmm.

03:51.440 --> 03:54.191
Nope. Still sucks.
[groans, coughs]

03:54.193 --> 03:57.778
But for this year, my menu
is already up on the fridge.

03:57.780 --> 03:59.488
And it really means a lot to me.

03:59.490 --> 04:02.741
It's our first thanksgiving
with maggie.

04:02.743 --> 04:05.661
I'm finally not pregnant,
so I can drink.

04:05.663 --> 04:06.912
I call a drumstick.

04:06.914 --> 04:08.455
Nice try, boy,

04:08.457 --> 04:10.374
But we agreed I'd get
both drumsticks

04:10.376 --> 04:12.209
Every thanksgiving
on the day you were born.

04:12.211 --> 04:15.003
Aw, no fair.
I was too young to sign that.

04:15.005 --> 04:18.131
I believe this is
your foot, is it not?

04:18.133 --> 04:22.210
-And I had it notarized.
-Why you giant...

04:22.212 --> 04:24.263
-[grunting]
-[chocking]

04:24.265 --> 04:25.555
[sighs]

04:25.557 --> 04:27.766
[lisa]
<i> but the worst was yet to come.</i>

04:27.768 --> 04:31.395
<i>That thanksgiving would surpass</i>
<i> christmas and my birthday</i>

04:31.397 --> 04:33.855
<i>As the saddest day of the year.</i>

04:33.857 --> 04:36.024
[hawaiian music playing]

04:39.029 --> 04:41.280
[slurping]

04:43.409 --> 04:47.619
Welcome, or as they say
in hawaii: Welcome.

04:47.621 --> 04:50.330
You're probably wondering
why we chose this special day

04:50.332 --> 04:53.417
To have this celebration of you,
my workers

04:53.419 --> 04:56.461
And dear, dear friends.
[chuckles]

04:56.463 --> 04:59.998
Smithers, I need a distraction
so those unionized money-sucks

05:00.000 --> 05:01.925
Don't see the new
cheaper replacements

05:01.927 --> 05:04.052
I'm bringing in
to take their jobs.

05:04.054 --> 05:05.804
Why don't we throw
a hawaiian day?

05:05.806 --> 05:09.141
Aloha-ha-ha-ha.

05:09.143 --> 05:12.519
Now enjoy, relax, mahalo,

05:12.521 --> 05:15.772
Knowing your jobs are secure
and I could never replace you.

05:15.774 --> 05:17.316
[cheering, laughing]

05:17.318 --> 05:19.693
Nothing ulterior
about that statement.

05:19.695 --> 05:21.528
We love you!

05:21.530 --> 05:24.948
That's the last
we'll see of them.

05:25.701 --> 05:27.534
Welcome, nonunion workers.

05:27.536 --> 05:30.454
In an older era,
they'd call you scabs.

05:30.456 --> 05:33.373
Now you're just friends
without benefits.

05:33.375 --> 05:34.333
[chuckles]

05:34.335 --> 05:36.543
[machines whirring rhythmically]

05:37.796 --> 05:40.339
♪

05:46.096 --> 05:48.263
♪<i> see here, smithers,</i>
<i> here's my theory</i> ♪

05:48.265 --> 05:50.307
♪<i> of how to cut down</i>
<i> what people earn</i> ♪

05:50.309 --> 05:52.434
♪<i> every worker</i>
<i> should be nonunion</i> ♪

05:52.436 --> 05:54.853
♪<i> that's the genius</i>
<i> of monty burns</i> ♪

05:54.855 --> 05:57.064
[tap dancing]

06:02.613 --> 06:05.405
♪<i> they've got no health care,</i>
<i> they've got no dental</i> ♪

06:05.407 --> 06:07.115
♪<i> there's just one bathroom,</i>
<i> so they take turns</i> ♪

06:07.117 --> 06:09.159
♪<i> and all the money</i>
<i> and all the power</i> ♪

06:09.161 --> 06:11.536
♪<i> are in the clutches</i>
<i> of monty burns</i> ♪

06:11.538 --> 06:13.580
♪<i> hallelujah</i> ♪

06:13.582 --> 06:15.832
♪<i> make us grovel</i> ♪

06:15.834 --> 06:17.793
♪<i> for your energy</i> ♪

06:17.795 --> 06:19.628
♪<i> speed up the core,</i>
<i> speed up the core, man</i> ♪

06:19.630 --> 06:21.963
♪<i> speed up the core, speed up</i>
<i> the core, man</i> ♪

06:21.965 --> 06:23.799
♪<i> speed up the, speed up the,</i>
<i> speed up the, speed up</i> ♪

06:23.801 --> 06:26.134
♪<i> the core</i> ♪

06:26.136 --> 06:28.095
♪<i> rig detectors</i>
<i> and bribe inspectors</i> ♪

06:28.097 --> 06:30.180
♪<i> skip the training</i>
<i> 'cause no one learns</i> ♪

06:30.182 --> 06:31.932
♪<i> even people</i>
<i> who ain't too clever</i> ♪

06:31.934 --> 06:34.351
♪<i> can work for minimum wage</i>
<i> forever</i> ♪

06:34.353 --> 06:35.769
♪<i> broken parts can be</i>
<i> glued together</i> ♪

06:35.771 --> 06:38.313
♪<i> for monty burns</i> ♪

06:38.315 --> 06:42.109
♪<i> monty burns, monty burns</i> ♪

06:42.111 --> 06:49.032
♪<i> monty burns.</i> ♪

06:49.034 --> 06:50.200
[cheering]

06:51.495 --> 06:56.164
Smithers, how do these nonunion
avocado toasts sing so well?

06:56.166 --> 06:57.999
Oh, they're all graduates of

06:58.001 --> 06:59.376
Prestigious college
theater programs.

06:59.378 --> 07:02.421
-Ah.
-That entire section
is julliard.

07:02.423 --> 07:06.258
[harmonizing]
♪<i> it's this or teach.</i> ♪

07:07.219 --> 07:09.678
♪

07:15.644 --> 07:17.310
Somebody should clean these up.

07:17.312 --> 07:19.771
I nominate king kamehameha.

07:19.773 --> 07:22.399
I'm starting to think
this king thing is just a trick

07:22.401 --> 07:24.359
To get me to do all the work.

07:24.361 --> 07:27.696
No, no. It's a very great honor,
your gullibility.

07:27.698 --> 07:29.281
[laughter]

07:29.283 --> 07:31.324
[grunting]

07:32.327 --> 07:33.785
Hmm. [grunts]

07:33.787 --> 07:36.329
Mm, mm.

07:37.332 --> 07:41.501
Whew! Not gonna make
that mistake.

07:42.588 --> 07:45.297
[automated voice]
<i> waste disposed safely.</i>

07:45.299 --> 07:47.174
Thank you.

07:47.676 --> 07:50.510
Now to call
jeff bezos and elon musk

07:50.512 --> 07:52.137
And reclaim my title of

07:52.139 --> 07:53.930
The world's most
self-serving billionaire.

07:53.932 --> 07:56.391
Where can I plug in my phone?

07:57.186 --> 07:59.186
[electrical crackling]

07:59.188 --> 08:02.731
Uh, sir, I'm afraid we already
over-amped on that outlet.

08:02.733 --> 08:04.649
I'll over-amp you.

08:04.651 --> 08:06.109
[crackling]

08:06.528 --> 08:07.652
[whooshing]

08:08.614 --> 08:09.863
Put it out! Put it out!

08:09.865 --> 08:12.407
♪<i> we don't know how.</i> ♪

08:12.409 --> 08:16.077
But we can dance stravinsky's
"firebird" around it.

08:16.079 --> 08:18.455
["the firebird" playing]

08:20.542 --> 08:22.542
[alarm blaring]

08:23.587 --> 08:25.003
[panicked shouting]

08:25.005 --> 08:27.130
[squealing]

08:28.217 --> 08:30.175
Homer, what did you do in there?

08:30.177 --> 08:32.594
I did exactly
what I was supposed to do.

08:32.596 --> 08:34.930
[automated voice over speakers]
<i> attention, plant employees.</i>

08:34.932 --> 08:36.765
See? She'll tell you.

08:36.767 --> 08:38.266
<i> Plant meltdown imminent.</i>

08:38.268 --> 08:41.311
<i> Please take this time</i>
<i> to get right with your god.</i>

08:41.313 --> 08:43.355
♪

08:47.778 --> 08:50.570
<i> Now please put your name tag</i>
<i> inside your mouth</i>

08:50.572 --> 08:53.782
<i> For the easy identification</i>
<i> of your skull.</i>

08:53.784 --> 08:55.492
[panicked shouting]

09:01.667 --> 09:02.582
[alarm continues blaring]

09:02.584 --> 09:03.959
Where are you going?

09:03.961 --> 09:05.585
Uh, to get help.

09:08.131 --> 09:10.173
Don't leave me, uncle monty!

09:11.134 --> 09:13.677
-Smithers,
did you grease the struts?
-Yes, sir.

09:13.679 --> 09:15.554
[screaming]

09:20.519 --> 09:24.145
Yarr... You kidding me?!

09:25.190 --> 09:26.898
[automated voice]
<i> fire extinguished.</i>

09:26.900 --> 09:28.191
<i> Plant ruined,</i>

09:28.193 --> 09:30.360
<i>And you are all now out of work.</i>

09:30.362 --> 09:32.988
<i> -Happy thanksgiving.</i>
-[toots]

09:37.869 --> 09:42.163
[lisa]
<i> we had no power</i>
<i>and no prospects of getting any.</i>

09:44.084 --> 09:45.125
[crowd cheering]

09:45.127 --> 09:46.251
[crowd gasping]

09:46.253 --> 09:48.587
-What is it? What is it?
-We'll never know!

09:48.589 --> 09:51.548
[lisa]
<i> but whenever there's</i>
<i> a threat to civilization,</i>

09:51.550 --> 09:54.626
<i> Good people always</i>
<i> set aside their differences</i>

09:54.628 --> 09:56.928
<i> And blame a scapegoat.</i>

09:56.930 --> 09:59.514
All right, so,
who screwed up here?

09:59.516 --> 10:00.432
Homer?

10:00.434 --> 10:03.560
[chanting]
homer. Homer. Homer.

10:03.562 --> 10:04.769
I agree.

10:04.771 --> 10:07.981
We should find a scapegoat,
but who?

10:07.983 --> 10:09.899
[chanting]
you. You. You.

10:09.901 --> 10:11.484
I can't believe this.

10:11.486 --> 10:12.652
I love you guys,

10:12.654 --> 10:14.779
And now you want to
throw me under the bus?

10:14.781 --> 10:16.698
Great idea.

10:18.452 --> 10:19.951
Hey!

10:19.953 --> 10:22.370
"throwing someone under the bus"
is a figure of speech.

10:22.372 --> 10:24.372
Like, "I'll start my diet
tomorrow,"

10:24.374 --> 10:26.166
Or "I love my children equally."

10:26.168 --> 10:28.084
Okay, homer. Fair enough.

10:28.086 --> 10:29.628
Ten-second head start!

10:29.630 --> 10:31.338
Ten, nine, eight, seven...

10:31.340 --> 10:34.591
You could've at least
done mississippi!

10:34.593 --> 10:36.301
[wind whistling]

10:37.304 --> 10:39.763
-[door rattles]
-[gasps] who's there?

10:39.765 --> 10:41.389
♪

10:41.391 --> 10:43.975
Watch it. I have pepper spray.

10:43.977 --> 10:46.436
[homer]
mmm... Pepper spray.

10:46.438 --> 10:47.687
[salivating]

10:47.689 --> 10:49.064
Homer?

10:49.066 --> 10:50.690
I put in all the storm windows,

10:50.692 --> 10:53.985
And I bought brand-new batteries
for all the flashlights.

10:53.987 --> 10:56.237
-Huh? Huh?
-[gasps]

10:56.239 --> 10:58.740
[lisa]
<i> there was nothing</i>
<i> that alarmed my mother more</i>

10:58.742 --> 11:01.159
<i> Than a helpful homer.</i>

11:01.161 --> 11:03.995
Homer simpson,
did you have anything to do

11:03.997 --> 11:05.246
With the blackout?

11:05.248 --> 11:07.207
Everybody thinks I did,
but I didn't.

11:07.209 --> 11:10.502
But I don't care because
you believe, marge, don't you?

11:10.504 --> 11:12.462
I'm trying.

11:13.256 --> 11:14.631
Eh. Could've been worse.

11:14.633 --> 11:15.799
[cries out]

11:15.801 --> 11:18.343
Once again,
the whole town is mad at dad.

11:18.345 --> 11:21.012
Bart, do you know
how many furious mobs

11:21.014 --> 11:23.390
The average family
has to contend with?

11:23.392 --> 11:24.474
Hmm, six?

11:24.476 --> 11:26.559
Zero. Zero!

11:26.561 --> 11:28.269
You did do this.

11:28.271 --> 11:31.690
Marge, in every marriage,
a spouse gets to say one time,

11:31.692 --> 11:34.025
"you have got to believe me."

11:34.027 --> 11:36.444
Yes, and you've done it
18 times.

11:36.446 --> 11:38.530
Look in my eyes.

11:38.532 --> 11:40.031
You've said that before.

11:40.033 --> 11:44.077
Hold my hand
and look in my eyes.

11:44.079 --> 11:45.787
You've said that before.

11:45.789 --> 11:50.208
Hold my hand, look in my eyes
and feel my heart.

11:50.210 --> 11:53.002
Also, if you can
examine my prostate...

11:53.004 --> 11:55.046
All right, all right.

11:55.048 --> 11:57.215
[grunting]

11:57.718 --> 12:00.093
I don't know.

12:01.680 --> 12:03.263
Mom!

12:03.265 --> 12:05.390
I was aiming for his eye.

12:05.392 --> 12:08.601
Mom, dad, please give us hope.

12:08.603 --> 12:10.895
It's what parents do.

12:10.897 --> 12:13.398
Don't worry, kids.
The government will help.

12:13.400 --> 12:15.650
The government cannot
help itself,

12:15.652 --> 12:17.026
Let alone you.

12:17.028 --> 12:19.529
I have just been authorized
to commission a study

12:19.531 --> 12:23.032
On whether or not a study
should be commissioned.

12:23.034 --> 12:24.534
Finally. Thank you.

12:24.536 --> 12:27.203
So, to take your minds
off your troubles,

12:27.205 --> 12:29.205
I propose some kind of games.

12:29.207 --> 12:31.124
Either "hunger" or "squid."

12:31.126 --> 12:33.084
With that in mind,
tomorrow we will begin

12:33.086 --> 12:35.670
With everyone attempting
to kill milhouse.

12:35.672 --> 12:37.797
I finally got picked first.

12:37.799 --> 12:39.382
Boo-yeah!

12:39.384 --> 12:41.426
-[tires screeching]
-[man grunting]

12:41.428 --> 12:42.969
[woman] take this.

12:46.099 --> 12:48.183
[people talking angrily
outside]

12:49.144 --> 12:52.771
No laptop, no kindle.
What do I do?

12:52.773 --> 12:55.231
[gasps] I'll read a book.

12:56.401 --> 12:57.233
Hmm.

12:57.235 --> 12:58.818
I might learn something.

12:58.820 --> 13:00.820
This pioneer girl was happy.

13:00.822 --> 13:02.614
I'm not happy.

13:02.616 --> 13:03.990
This is a nightmare.

13:03.992 --> 13:05.950
My pa moved us out of wisconsin

13:05.952 --> 13:07.827
Because he thought
it was too fancy.

13:07.829 --> 13:09.037
Wisconsin?

13:09.039 --> 13:11.331
And before you want to be me,

13:11.333 --> 13:12.707
Answer this:

13:12.709 --> 13:14.959
Did you ever kill a chicken?

13:14.961 --> 13:17.253
Sorry, I'm a vegetarian.

13:17.255 --> 13:18.797
So was I.

13:18.799 --> 13:22.008
[lisa]
<i> that as the moment</i>
<i> I began my remembrance book.</i>

13:22.010 --> 13:25.136
<i> [in frontier accent]</i>
<i> and in my memory,</i>
<i> I sound like this.</i>

13:25.138 --> 13:28.348
<i> People were made of</i>
<i>stronger stuff in pioneer days,</i>

13:28.350 --> 13:31.518
<i>Until they died of agony at 39.</i>

13:31.520 --> 13:32.894
[wind whistling]

13:32.896 --> 13:36.231
Well, if nothing else,
I can try to save thanksgiving.

13:36.233 --> 13:39.359
[gasps] the food is gone.

13:39.361 --> 13:42.529
Homer, is there an explanation?

13:42.531 --> 13:43.863
Yes, there is.

13:43.865 --> 13:45.698
-I--
-no more explanations.

13:45.700 --> 13:49.077
I can't take it. [sobbing]

13:49.079 --> 13:52.789
Dad, I'm really sad.
What do I do?

13:52.791 --> 13:54.165
I don't know. Go outside.

13:54.167 --> 13:56.626
-Build a snowman.
-I can't bring another life

13:56.628 --> 13:58.044
Into this awful world.

13:58.046 --> 14:00.046
-Shoo!
-[moans]

14:00.048 --> 14:01.923
I have a little juice.

14:01.925 --> 14:03.675
I can call tech support.

14:03.677 --> 14:05.844
[ropes creaking]

14:05.846 --> 14:07.512
[groans]

14:07.514 --> 14:08.346
[grunts]

14:08.348 --> 14:10.098
You think you miss the internet?

14:10.100 --> 14:11.975
[bell clanging]

14:11.977 --> 14:13.601
Hear ye, hear ye.

14:13.603 --> 14:16.896
The latest<i> matrix</i> movie
was severely disappointing.

14:16.898 --> 14:19.190
Do not take the red pill
or the blue pill.

14:19.192 --> 14:21.401
You need no dose for this one.

14:21.403 --> 14:22.902
End of "tweet."

14:22.904 --> 14:24.362
Hey, like.

14:24.364 --> 14:27.073
In fact,
I'm going to "follow" you.

14:27.075 --> 14:28.825
-[scatting]
-yes, mute.

14:28.827 --> 14:30.869
-♪<i> giving you likes</i>
<i> and following you</i> ♪
-mute, mute.

14:30.871 --> 14:32.495
[scatting]

14:32.497 --> 14:35.415
[ragtime piano playing]

14:36.710 --> 14:38.459
[piano music stops]

14:40.505 --> 14:43.798
You! How dare you show your face
in here.

14:43.800 --> 14:45.174
Moe, it's me.

14:45.176 --> 14:46.926
And beneath all the drinking
and the jokes,

14:46.928 --> 14:48.761
We have a real relationship.

14:48.763 --> 14:50.096
And that means something.

14:50.098 --> 14:51.347
What are you getting at?

14:51.349 --> 14:52.432
Come on, man.

14:52.434 --> 14:55.435
Deep down, we kind of
love each other.

14:57.814 --> 14:59.314
Love you, too.

15:01.067 --> 15:01.941
[homer moans]

15:01.943 --> 15:03.359
It's hopeless.

15:03.361 --> 15:05.895
Everyone in this town hates us.

15:05.897 --> 15:09.407
But some not as much.
I brought firewood.

15:10.952 --> 15:13.369
Whoa, grampa.
How'd you score that?

15:13.371 --> 15:17.040
For your information, I grew up
in a cruel world like this,

15:17.042 --> 15:20.543
Back in the '30s or '50s,
or whatever makes sense now.

15:20.545 --> 15:24.088
[laughs] now let me get
that fire going for you.

15:27.469 --> 15:29.093
[all]
ah!

15:29.095 --> 15:31.554
Grampa, you saved us!

15:31.556 --> 15:35.141
[chuckles] well, old people
have a lot of wisdom

15:35.143 --> 15:36.434
If you take the time to--

15:36.436 --> 15:38.394
She said thank you.

15:39.439 --> 15:41.773
[jaunty tune playing

15:41.775 --> 15:43.650
<i> [lisa, in frontier accent]</i>
<i> we were more than happy.</i>

15:43.652 --> 15:45.485
<i> We were a family again.</i>

15:45.487 --> 15:47.528
♪

15:50.984 --> 15:52.408
[thumping]

15:52.410 --> 15:54.035
Oh, what was that?

15:54.037 --> 15:55.870
Go back to sleep, sweetie.

15:55.872 --> 15:57.330
Tomorrow's Sunday.

15:57.332 --> 16:00.917
You don't have to start
your chores till 4:00 a.M.

16:00.919 --> 16:03.962
[yawns] thanks, grampa.

16:03.964 --> 16:06.381
[truck engine starting]

16:06.383 --> 16:09.926
We'll finally be rid of that
homer simpson once and for all.

16:09.928 --> 16:12.470
And then I'll be the town idiot.

16:12.472 --> 16:14.430
[chuckles] mm.

16:15.725 --> 16:17.725
♪

16:24.067 --> 16:26.192
[creaking]

16:29.406 --> 16:31.447
[creaking]

16:31.449 --> 16:35.785
Oh, my god! "city celebrates
explosion of the simpsons."

16:35.787 --> 16:36.869
[marge groaning]

16:36.871 --> 16:39.747
That's "expulsion"
of the simpsons.

16:39.749 --> 16:40.957
Oh, whew.

16:40.959 --> 16:42.625
Which means they
kicked us out forever.

16:42.627 --> 16:43.710
Damn it!

16:43.712 --> 16:45.920
Why won't people
believe I'm innocent?

16:45.922 --> 16:47.588
-[creaking]
-oh, it's hopeless.

16:47.590 --> 16:50.258
-[yowling]
-whoa, cool!

16:52.846 --> 16:54.679
[playing jaunty tune]

16:54.681 --> 16:57.098
[sighs] I guess there's
one good thing.

16:57.100 --> 16:58.683
At least there's
no more stupid--

16:58.685 --> 17:00.018
Howdy, neighbor.

17:00.020 --> 17:02.478
I asked them to move my house
right next to yours.

17:02.480 --> 17:03.980
[homer groans]

17:05.150 --> 17:08.234
Well, at least you
believe me, flanders.

17:08.236 --> 17:11.738
Yes, but I also believe in
a holy ghost no one can see.

17:11.740 --> 17:14.574
In the name of the father and
the son and the spooky plus one.

17:14.576 --> 17:17.493
[groans] I haven't slept
for two nights.

17:17.495 --> 17:21.330
Because my choice is either to
be furious at you for the lie,

17:21.332 --> 17:24.459
Or to believe you
and feel like a fool.

17:24.461 --> 17:25.960
[groans]

17:25.962 --> 17:28.546
Okay, okay,
I'm going to believe it.

17:28.548 --> 17:29.380
[gulps]

17:29.382 --> 17:32.842
Ugh. Now I'm actually in pain.

17:32.844 --> 17:34.093
No pain, no gain.

17:34.095 --> 17:36.596
I can't go on faith anymore.

17:36.598 --> 17:41.059
I have to have a reason
to believe you. [groans]

17:41.061 --> 17:42.643
There is. Oh, my god.

17:42.645 --> 17:45.396
Do you remember when you thought
I ate the food in the fridge?

17:45.398 --> 17:46.522
Yes?

17:46.524 --> 17:47.648
Well, I didn't.

17:47.650 --> 17:50.276
I put it under the snow
to keep it fresh.

17:50.278 --> 17:52.528
Like in lisa's
stupid pioneer book.

17:52.530 --> 17:53.780
Oh, my god.

17:53.782 --> 17:55.656
[gasps]
you're telling the truth.

17:55.658 --> 17:57.575
And if you're telling
the truth about that,

17:57.577 --> 18:00.161
-Then you're telling the truth
about everything!
-Mm-hmm.

18:00.163 --> 18:03.581
-Oh. [laughing]
-mm.

18:03.583 --> 18:05.249
-Ooh, homie.
-[chuckling]

18:05.251 --> 18:06.918
But if you're an innocent idiot,

18:06.920 --> 18:08.586
Instead of a guilty nitwit,

18:08.588 --> 18:09.879
How do we prove it?

18:09.881 --> 18:12.090
By finding the person
who was behind it.

18:12.092 --> 18:14.425
And there's only one man
who it could be.

18:14.427 --> 18:16.260
The town villain.

18:16.262 --> 18:17.428
Luigi!

18:17.430 --> 18:19.013
No! Burns!

18:20.058 --> 18:22.767
Smithers, I've eluded justice
yet again.

18:22.769 --> 18:24.894
May my uppance never come.

18:24.896 --> 18:26.562
[marge]
not so fast!

18:26.564 --> 18:27.563
Gah!

18:27.565 --> 18:29.398
We know what you did.

18:29.400 --> 18:34.070
Yes, but you're also standing
on top of my trap door.

18:35.198 --> 18:38.783
It, uh, doesn't work
without power, sir.

18:38.785 --> 18:41.285
Fine. Smithers, do it manually.

18:42.789 --> 18:44.997
[clicking]

18:45.834 --> 18:48.876
[burns cackles]

18:48.878 --> 18:50.837
You can't move.
That's cheating.

18:50.839 --> 18:52.588
Take him away, boys.

18:55.009 --> 18:57.510
Get the kiddie cuffs, lou.

18:57.512 --> 18:59.387
Curses!

19:01.224 --> 19:04.016
I have to take responsibility
for something I did?

19:04.018 --> 19:06.060
[chuckles] ridiculous.

19:08.314 --> 19:12.108
Montgomery burns, we will give
you the stiffest punishment

19:12.110 --> 19:13.901
Any billionaire ever gets.

19:13.903 --> 19:16.737
A fine you can easily pay.

19:17.949 --> 19:19.157
I make more than that
in the time

19:19.159 --> 19:22.201
It took me to say
"I make more than that." ha!

19:22.203 --> 19:25.163
I'm so glad you guys
love me again.

19:25.165 --> 19:27.039
We're still a little mad.

19:27.041 --> 19:28.374
This brought back
a lot of memories

19:28.376 --> 19:30.293
Of stuff you actually did do.

19:30.295 --> 19:32.670
Remember, homer, I was
gonna be an orthodontist.

19:32.672 --> 19:34.422
But no more, thanks to you.

19:34.424 --> 19:37.466
What if you all have
thanksgiving dinner with us?

19:37.468 --> 19:41.304
All you have to do is put
our house back where it was.

19:41.306 --> 19:44.515
It's never just dinner.
There's always something.

19:46.561 --> 19:48.644
♪

19:53.401 --> 19:55.318
<i> [lisa, in frontier accent]</i>
<i>and in the years that followed,</i>

19:55.320 --> 19:58.070
<i> There would be other blackouts</i>
<i> and other mobs.</i>

19:58.072 --> 20:01.032
<i> But they never blamed</i>
<i> my father again.</i>

20:01.034 --> 20:03.534
-Bart?
-Your story was so long

20:03.536 --> 20:04.869
I died of boredom.

20:04.871 --> 20:07.413
Also, I finally got a drumstick.

20:07.415 --> 20:08.831
Mine now.

20:08.833 --> 20:10.374
